<li id="cite_note-50"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50" title="">^</a></b> The Worth of Human Life is Unquestionable; by Shmully Hecht, <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20060302071054/http://www.yaledailynews.com/article.asp?AID=2428" class="external text" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20060302071054/http://www.yaledailynews.com/article.asp?AID=2428" rel="nofollow">Archive copy</a> at the <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archive" title="Internet Archive">Internet Archive</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-51"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.ncd.gov/newsroom/testimony/ncd_4-17-99.html" class="external text" title="http://www.ncd.gov/newsroom/testimony/ncd_4-17-99.html" rel="nofollow">Statement of Marca Bistro, chairperson, National council on disability: regarding the hiring of Peter Singer</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-52"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.thearclink.org/news/article.asp?ID=426" class="external text" title="http://www.thearclink.org/news/article.asp?ID=426" rel="nofollow">Against the Philosophy of Peter Singer&#160;— Mental Retardation and Developmental Disabilities Services</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-53"><b><a href="#cite_ref-53" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.newcriterion.com/articles.cfm/bolivian-daniels-2161" class="external text" title="http://www.newcriterion.com/articles.cfm/bolivian-daniels-2161" rel="nofollow">How to murder a Bolivian boy</a> by <a href="/wiki/Anthony_Daniels_(psychiatrist)" title="Anthony Daniels (psychiatrist)">Anthony Daniels</a>, <a href="/wiki/The_New_Criterion" title="The New Criterion">The New Criterion</a>, Vol. 19, No. 10, June 2001</li>
<li id="cite_note-54"><b><a href="#cite_ref-54" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.re-public.gr/en/?p=154" class="external text" title="http://www.re-public.gr/en/?p=154" rel="nofollow">Animals, humans, persons: Problematic implications of Singer’s notion of “animal rights”</a> by Josef Bordat</li>
<li id="cite_note-55"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55" title="">^</a></b> <i>The Expanding Circle: Ethics and Sociobiology</i>, New York: Farrar, Straus and Giroux, 1981, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0374234965" class="internal">ISBN 0-374-23496-5</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-56"><b><a href="#cite_ref-56" title="">^</a></b> <i>The Expanding Circle</i> p. 93</li>
<li id="cite_note-57"><b><a href="#cite_ref-57" title="">^</a></b> <i>The Expanding Circle</i> p. 119</li>
<li id="cite_note-58"><b><a href="#cite_ref-58" title="">^</a></b> Ken Binmore, <i>Natural Justice</i>, Oxford&#160;: Oxford University Press, 2005. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0195178114" class="internal">ISBN 0-19-517811-4</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-59"><b><a href="#cite_ref-59" title="">^</a></b> In, e.g., the last chapter of <i>Practical Ethics</i>.</li>
</ol>
